Στάλθηκε από Copilot:
Sure! Here’s a simple way to create an HTML page that displays all images from a directory. Let’s assume your images are in a folder named images.

Create the HTML File:
Create a new file named index.html in your project directory.
Write the HTML Code:
Open index.html in a text editor and add the following code:
HTML

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Image Gallery</title>
    <style>
        body {
            display: flex;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            justify-content: center;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
        }
        img {
            margin: 10px;
            border: 2px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 8px;
            max-width: 200px;
            max-height: 200px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Image Gallery</h1>
    <div id="gallery">
        <!-- Images will be inserted here -->
    </div>
    <script>
        const images = [
            'images/photo1.jpg',
            'images/photo2.jpg',
            'images/photo3.jpg'
            // Add more image paths here
        ];

        const gallery = document.getElementById('gallery');

        images.forEach(src => {
            const img = document.createElement('img');
            img.src = src;
            img.alt = 'Image';
            gallery.appendChild(img);
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
